WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.504
♪

00:04.671 --> 00:06.131
FELIX:
So, I put on my boxers,

00:06.131 --> 00:07.591
and then I realize that
I put it on backwards,

00:07.591 --> 00:09.009
so the fly is in the back.

00:09.009 --> 00:10.552
And then it came to me--
VICTOR: Mm-hm.

00:10.552 --> 00:13.180
- Butt fly, right?
- Yeah.

00:16.225 --> 00:18.227
- So, your sister's still mad at me?

00:19.853 --> 00:23.273
- Yeah, she's never really
been one for subtlety.
- Yeah.

00:25.192 --> 00:28.111
- That's Benji. Hide me, hide me!
- Oh, okay. Why, why?!

00:28.111 --> 00:29.863
- Because I don't want
to talk to him right now.

00:29.863 --> 00:33.158
Make yourself bigger!
- How? I am naturally dainty.

00:33.158 --> 00:33.992
Okay!

00:35.244 --> 00:36.453
Uh, what was that?

00:37.329 --> 00:39.540
- I saw Benji last night,
which was great,

00:39.540 --> 00:42.417
until his dad showed up,
and told me to stay away from him.

00:43.210 --> 00:47.214
- Well, join the club.
We're bad boys now, Victor.

00:47.881 --> 00:50.884
Should we start a club?
The Daddy Don't Like Me Squad?

00:50.884 --> 00:53.095
- He said that I was bad for Benji.

00:54.513 --> 00:56.390
And that I "create chaos."

00:56.390 --> 01:00.811
- Okay, that is absurd.
You, my friend, are a ray of light.

01:01.436 --> 01:05.065
- Thanks, man, but I don't know.
I'm startin' to think maybe he's right.

01:05.732 --> 01:07.484
I feel like everyone
I'm close to, I wind up hurting.

01:07.484 --> 01:08.861
- Okay, name one person.

01:08.861 --> 01:10.445
- Mia.

01:10.445 --> 01:13.156
- You were figuring out your sexuality.
That's your God-given right.

01:13.156 --> 01:14.491
- Okay, Rahim.

01:14.491 --> 01:17.286
- You were... choosing between
two hotties. That happens.

01:17.286 --> 01:19.496
- And then, of course,
there's, there's Benji.

01:20.372 --> 01:22.624
Like, all of my family stuff
was so stressful

01:22.624 --> 01:24.251
that he wound up relapsing.

01:25.043 --> 01:26.503
- Okay, yeah, when you
lay it out like that,

01:26.503 --> 01:29.131
you do sound a teensy bit
like an agent of chaos.

01:29.131 --> 01:31.675
- Yeah, I know.
- Do you guys mind keeping
the personal banter down?

01:31.675 --> 01:33.677
- Class hasn't even started yet, Liam.

01:34.428 --> 01:36.388
God. It's like he wants
people to hate him.

01:36.388 --> 01:38.432
- Good morning, class!

01:38.432 --> 01:42.769
Today, we will begin
an exciting new group project

01:42.769 --> 01:45.147
exploring protein synthesis.

01:45.147 --> 01:46.648
[all groan]

01:46.648 --> 01:48.483
Ya think this is my dream morning?

01:48.483 --> 01:49.735
I wanted to be a dancer.

01:50.235 --> 01:52.446
All right, everyone,
choose groups of three.

01:57.743 --> 01:59.828
- Hey... why don't we
partner up with Liam?

02:01.580 --> 02:04.249
I mean, I, I know he's a little--
- Horrible, yeah.

02:04.249 --> 02:05.834
- Well, he just looks so lonely.

02:05.834 --> 02:09.254
- No, you're trying to do a mitzvah
to prove you're not an agent of chaos.

02:09.254 --> 02:10.297
- What's a mitzvah?

02:11.215 --> 02:13.425
- Dude, we really need to get
you on the Mrs. Maisel train.

02:13.425 --> 02:15.886
- Hey, Liam...
Do you wanna be our partner?

02:16.970 --> 02:19.223
- Really? Thanks.

02:19.932 --> 02:22.351
Ah, you know, I'm gonna ask
the guidance counselor

02:22.351 --> 02:25.354
if working with you two dummies
counts as community service.

02:30.609 --> 02:31.485
- Oh my god.

02:31.860 --> 02:34.571
♪ Somebody to tell me it'll be alright ♪

02:34.571 --> 02:37.491
♪ Somebody to tell me it'll be just fine ♪

02:37.491 --> 02:39.493
♪ If someone has been there before ♪

02:39.493 --> 02:43.121
♪ Say it right now,
'cause I just need to hear it ♪

02:48.961 --> 02:51.755
[indistinct chatter]

02:51.755 --> 02:54.591
- So, I just took another
SAT practice test

02:54.591 --> 02:56.760
and the results were... not pretty.

02:56.760 --> 02:57.928
- But you're pretty.

02:57.928 --> 03:00.347
- Aww, cute, but not helpful.

03:01.265 --> 03:05.143
Wanna do a study sesh tonight?
We can make some flashcards.

03:05.143 --> 03:07.062
Please?
- Okay, fine.

03:07.604 --> 03:08.438
You guys?

03:08.981 --> 03:11.942
- Oh, absolutely not.
My jump shot is my SAT.

03:11.942 --> 03:14.152
[phone ringing]
- Uh, sorry. One second.

03:15.404 --> 03:16.238
Hi.

03:17.364 --> 03:18.198
What?!

03:18.907 --> 03:20.784
Wha-- Um, I-- Wait, I thought,

03:20.784 --> 03:23.203
I thought she wasn't due
for another three weeks.

03:24.872 --> 03:28.125
Um, oh, yeah, of course, um.

03:28.125 --> 03:29.793
Call me when you can.

03:30.335 --> 03:31.461
Love you.

03:34.381 --> 03:35.424
Veronica's in labor.

03:35.424 --> 03:38.844
[Lake gasps]
- Whoa, Baby Brooks comin' in hot!

03:40.220 --> 03:42.598
So, are you not excited about this?

03:42.598 --> 03:45.350
- Yeah, um, but I was
supposed to be there.

03:45.350 --> 03:47.186
You know, I, I booked my ticket
already and everything,

03:47.186 --> 03:49.062
and now I'm, I'm just
gonna miss the whole thing.

03:49.062 --> 03:50.606
- Right. So, you'll miss the birth.

03:50.606 --> 03:52.858
What's important is
you're gonna be a big sister.

03:52.858 --> 03:56.612
- Yeah, and since I'm your sister,
that means I'll be the baby's auntie.

03:56.612 --> 04:00.240
- Uh, wait, if you're my sister, wouldn't
that make you the baby's sister, too?

04:01.366 --> 04:02.784
- This is why I need to study.

04:06.330 --> 04:09.041
- Pilar... Hey, Pilar, Pilar, hey, hey.

04:09.041 --> 04:10.292
Um, look, I know you're pissed.

04:10.292 --> 04:12.085
I just-- I, I, I think
we should talk about it.

04:12.085 --> 04:14.087
- Okay, fine. Let's talk.
Do you wanna be with me,

04:14.087 --> 04:16.131
or are you still too scared
of making my dad angry?

04:16.131 --> 04:19.760
- To be fair, your dad's already angry.
I-I'm scared of making him angrier.

04:19.760 --> 04:21.178
- Goodbye, Felix.

04:22.721 --> 04:23.931
[sighs]

04:27.851 --> 04:33.065
- Oh, look, we are
eating lunch with Liam.

04:33.065 --> 04:35.234
You know, this day is
just getting better and better.

04:35.234 --> 04:37.569
- Well, I figured it'd be good
for us to get to know each other.

04:37.569 --> 04:39.821
- Okay, well, here's all you
need to know about me.
- Mm.

04:39.821 --> 04:41.990
- I have never gotten less
than an A on anything,

04:41.990 --> 04:43.367
and I don't intend to start now.

04:43.367 --> 04:45.369
I need to become valedictorian,
so that I can go to Harvard,

04:45.369 --> 04:48.121
and then, you know, obviously Harvard Law,

04:48.121 --> 04:49.873
and then, become the President.

04:49.873 --> 04:52.668
- Oh, well, you certainly
have the personality for it.

04:52.668 --> 04:54.086
[phone trills]

04:54.628 --> 04:56.255
- Um... Oh!

04:56.797 --> 04:59.883
Just remembered I actually have
an AP Lit quiz to cram for.

04:59.883 --> 05:03.136
I will see you two later.
- Um, yeah, see you later.

05:04.596 --> 05:05.806
Oh my god.

05:05.806 --> 05:07.808
- Hey, isn't that the sound
your gay dating app makes?

05:07.808 --> 05:10.060
- Liam is in the closet.

05:10.060 --> 05:12.271
That explains why he's so uptight
and pushes everyone away.

05:13.105 --> 05:16.275
- Oh, he's not a dick. He just wants dick.

05:16.275 --> 05:17.359
- He probably just needs
someone to talk to,

05:17.359 --> 05:18.777
and I could be that someone.

05:19.528 --> 05:20.612
I could be his Simon.

05:20.612 --> 05:24.032
- Oh yeah, that's right. Simon.
What ever happened to that guy?

05:26.994 --> 05:29.037
♪

05:29.037 --> 05:30.455
- Okay, mi lindo.

05:30.455 --> 05:35.544
What is the difference between
a dictatorship and an oligarchy?

05:35.544 --> 05:36.795
- No idea. What is it?

05:36.795 --> 05:41.091
- Oh... well, obviously, I know,

05:41.091 --> 05:43.760
but if I told you that would
be cheating, so look it up.

05:43.760 --> 05:45.971
- Hey, guys.
- Hi.

05:45.971 --> 05:47.014
- Oh, wow.

05:47.014 --> 05:48.974
No loud, angry music
coming from Pilar's room.

05:48.974 --> 05:51.435
- Yeah, she's not home.
I let her hang out with Rahim.

05:51.435 --> 05:52.436
- What?

05:52.895 --> 05:55.189
But we agreed she'd come
straight home after school.

05:55.189 --> 05:56.940
You can't just change
the rules without telling me.

05:56.940 --> 05:58.901
- I know, but our daughter
has been miserable

05:58.901 --> 06:02.529
since we forbid her to see Felix,
and I thought she needed a friend.

06:02.529 --> 06:05.032
- What she needs...
is to learn not to lie to us.

06:05.032 --> 06:06.867
Now, you call her right now
and tell her to come home.

06:06.867 --> 06:08.785
- Honey, I think it's okay.
- I don't care what you think.

06:08.785 --> 06:12.206
I'll call her myself if you won't do it.
- Fine. Go do it.

06:13.165 --> 06:16.001
I didn't realize that we
we're living in a dictatorship.

06:17.669 --> 06:20.297
Or an oligarchy. I lied.
I don't know the difference.

06:21.089 --> 06:23.759
♪

06:23.759 --> 06:26.094
- Ugh, these apps are a hellscape.

06:26.094 --> 06:27.638
Why can't I just have an old
fashioned "meet-cute"

06:27.638 --> 06:29.473
where a hot stranger and I
reach for the same kombucha

06:29.473 --> 06:31.517
in the grocery store?
Is that so hard to ask?

06:31.517 --> 06:33.143
- Enough!
- Oh my god, chill.

06:33.143 --> 06:35.354
I was, literally, complaining
for, like, a second.

06:35.354 --> 06:36.813
- Not you. Felix.

06:36.813 --> 06:38.690
He won't stop with the apology memes.

06:39.358 --> 06:41.485
I mean, either man up
and date me behind my father's back,

06:41.485 --> 06:42.528
or leave me alone.

06:42.528 --> 06:45.239
- I know we're mad at Felix,
but at least he has a face.

06:45.739 --> 06:46.949
- Mm.
- Mm-hm.

06:46.949 --> 06:49.868
[phone buzzing]
- Oh, good. The other guy I'm furious at.

06:51.912 --> 06:54.831
What?
ARMANDO [on phone]:
Come home right now, young lady.

06:54.831 --> 06:57.292
- I'm with Rahim. Mom said I could.
- I don't care what she said.

06:57.292 --> 06:59.169
I want you in your room in 15 minutes.

06:59.169 --> 07:00.170
- Goodbye.

07:00.921 --> 07:03.924
- Whoa... that was badass.

07:03.924 --> 07:06.510
Mom? Dayi? Uh.

07:08.470 --> 07:11.056
What are you doing here?
- Your uncle wanted coffee,

07:11.056 --> 07:15.602
and you're always raving about this place
and their chile mocha latte.

07:15.602 --> 07:19.898
- What is this ridiculous purple jacket?
This is a woman's jacket.

07:19.898 --> 07:24.152
- Uh, I--
- It's mine. I lent it to Rahim

07:24.152 --> 07:26.154
since it's so cold in here.

07:26.154 --> 07:28.490
- And you wanted to wear this?

07:29.241 --> 07:31.326
- Well, um--
- Yes...

07:31.326 --> 07:34.454
because Pilar is Rahim's girlfriend,

07:34.454 --> 07:38.083
and they share everything, even jackets.

07:39.710 --> 07:41.712
- Uh, Mom, can I talk to you for a second?
- Mm-hm.

07:42.254 --> 07:43.213
- So, you are his girlfriend?

07:43.213 --> 07:46.008
- I'm sorry, I panicked.

07:46.008 --> 07:47.843
He flies back to Tehran tomorrow.

07:47.843 --> 07:51.054
Let him think you have girlfriend, eh?
What's the harm?

07:51.972 --> 07:53.432
PILAR:
Okay, sure.

07:53.432 --> 07:54.725
Love to.
FARZAD: Great.

07:55.350 --> 07:57.561
Rahim, Pilar is wonderful.

07:57.561 --> 08:00.606
I invited her to my
farewell dinner tonight.

08:00.606 --> 08:03.817
Should we go try the chile mocha latte?
- Of course, of course.

08:06.653 --> 08:07.696
- It's fine.

08:07.696 --> 08:11.450
I'd rather be your fake girlfriend
than see my real father, so.

08:12.534 --> 08:14.536
♪

08:17.581 --> 08:18.415
[knocks on door]

08:20.250 --> 08:22.961
- Oh, hi! Come in.
You must be Victor's friend.

08:22.961 --> 08:25.422
- "Friend" is a bit much.
Let's go with colleague.

08:25.422 --> 08:29.843
- Okay... Victor, your colleague is here!
- Thanks.

08:29.843 --> 08:31.929
- Oh! Hey, Liam.
I'm so glad you could make it.

08:31.929 --> 08:34.431
- Yeah, like I said,
I just need to get an A on this project.

08:34.431 --> 08:35.599
Is Felix coming?

08:35.599 --> 08:37.643
- Um, no, no.
He's, he's not gonna be able to make it,

08:37.643 --> 08:39.853
um, but I just didn't want you
to do this project alone.

08:41.271 --> 08:42.523
You're not alone.

08:43.065 --> 08:44.858
- Okay, weirdo.

08:44.858 --> 08:46.527
Hey, do you have any
unsweetened iced tea?

08:46.527 --> 08:47.611
Don't answer that. Probably not.

08:47.611 --> 08:49.905
You seem like you're always
hyped up on refined sugar.

08:49.905 --> 08:51.114
Where is your room?

08:54.159 --> 08:55.786
- He's going through something.

09:00.165 --> 09:01.834
- She's still not home.

09:01.834 --> 09:04.795
I told her to come home
and she's just... not.

09:04.795 --> 09:06.839
We have totally lost control here.

09:06.839 --> 09:10.843
- Hm. I would weigh in here,
but since you don't care what I think.

09:13.512 --> 09:16.473
- I'm sorry I said that.
Of course, I care what you think.

09:16.473 --> 09:18.308
Okay? It's just that I'm

09:19.601 --> 09:21.019
so mad at Pilar.

09:21.979 --> 09:23.772
- Are you, Mando?
- Yes, of course.

09:23.772 --> 09:25.315
All the lying and sneaking around--

09:25.315 --> 09:29.361
- Is exactly what we were doing
when we were two teenagers in love.

09:29.361 --> 09:33.365
The way you're acting...
this isn't just overprotective dad.

09:34.533 --> 09:35.742
Makes me wonder

09:36.285 --> 09:38.704
if you're thinking about

09:39.788 --> 09:40.789
Camila.

09:43.625 --> 09:47.880
- What? No...
No, that's, that's not what this is about.

09:48.547 --> 09:49.548
- All right.

09:51.758 --> 09:53.760
♪

09:54.887 --> 09:58.390
- Hey, your dad is going to call
with an update as soon as he can.

09:58.390 --> 10:02.436
He's probably just...
massaging Veronica's placenta.

10:03.687 --> 10:05.606
- Ew, what?

10:06.565 --> 10:08.567
- Is that not something
people do during labor?

10:09.776 --> 10:12.613
- Okay, um, repudiate.

10:12.613 --> 10:15.240
- Easy. To pudiate something again.

10:15.699 --> 10:18.118
- You're adorable when
you're clueless, but no.

10:18.118 --> 10:21.663
Repudiate is "to refuse to accept."

10:21.663 --> 10:24.625
As in, "Every decent college
is going to repudiate us

10:24.625 --> 10:26.877
if we don't learn what
these frickin' words mean."

10:28.128 --> 10:29.129
- I need a break.

10:31.798 --> 10:34.176
- Do you think that he's not calling
because there's something wrong?

10:34.176 --> 10:36.303
Do you think that the hospital
would know to call me

10:36.303 --> 10:37.721
if there was something wrong?

10:38.555 --> 10:41.475
- I don't think that anything is wrong.

10:42.059 --> 10:44.436
- Yeah... you're probably right.

10:44.436 --> 10:45.521
- Yeah.

10:45.521 --> 10:47.940
- [sighs] I just can't believe
I'm missing this.

10:52.861 --> 10:54.404
[indistinct chatter]

10:54.404 --> 10:58.242
- So, Rahim, how did you
meet this lovely young lady?

10:58.784 --> 11:01.203
- Well, we spent the summer
working the same job

11:01.203 --> 11:02.829
selling pretzels at the mall.

11:02.829 --> 11:05.958
We bonded over our mutual
love for Billie Eilish,

11:05.958 --> 11:09.795
who is a very famous
American hockey player.

11:09.795 --> 11:11.964
- Ah.
- Yes, hockey.

11:11.964 --> 11:16.176
Our favorite sport
with the skating and pucks.

11:17.010 --> 11:20.639
- [grunts] Oh!
- Oh my god! This is a designer sweater.

11:21.306 --> 11:25.602
I mean, who cares about designer?
Not... this... bro.

11:25.602 --> 11:28.146
- I am so... so sorry.

11:29.189 --> 11:32.484
Hey, we've met before,
at that Creekwood girl's party.

11:32.484 --> 11:34.444
- Uh, sorry. I don't remember.

11:34.444 --> 11:39.449
- A-Actually, yeah, you spilled on me,
so... I guess now we're spill buddies.

11:39.449 --> 11:41.910
- Uh, can you please get
me some club soda?

11:41.910 --> 11:44.079
- Yeah, right on it.
- Thank you.

11:44.705 --> 11:48.542
- What was this party?
Not an American beer party.

11:48.542 --> 11:50.544
[speaking native language]

11:54.339 --> 11:57.342
- That waiter was hitting on you.
- What? No, he wasn't.

11:57.342 --> 12:00.053
- Of course, he was, dum-dum.
I mean, "spill buddies"?

12:00.053 --> 12:02.890
Nobody says anything that lame
unless they're crushing hard.

12:03.432 --> 12:06.768
- Oh my god, oh my god. You're right.
I spilled on him. He spilled on me.

12:06.768 --> 12:08.687
That was my meet-cute.
I just missed my meet-cute.

12:16.111 --> 12:18.697
- Uh, this is just a simple model
I made of the protein.

12:18.697 --> 12:21.325
Obviously, the real one
won't be so rudimentary.

12:21.325 --> 12:23.744
- Yeah, obviously.

12:23.744 --> 12:26.747
Um, hey, you know I'm gay, right?

12:26.747 --> 12:30.501
- Yeah, yeah. You stood up on a chair
and announced it to the whole school.

12:30.501 --> 12:32.628
Made me late for class.
[chuckles]

12:32.628 --> 12:36.924
- Yeah, um... well, before that,
I was in the closet,

12:36.924 --> 12:39.676
and I felt... really alone.

12:39.676 --> 12:41.929
And then I started
messaging this guy, Simon--

12:41.929 --> 12:43.388
- I'm sorry.
Why're you telling me all this?

12:44.556 --> 12:46.517
- Liam, I, I heard the app
on your phone today.

12:47.851 --> 12:49.561
- Oh, um--

12:49.561 --> 12:50.896
Well, it's not, it's not like I'm--

12:50.896 --> 12:53.398
- N-No, no, no. Liam, Liam, Liam.
- I just-- I, I, don't, like, do any--

12:53.398 --> 12:55.067
- It-it's, It's okay.

12:56.151 --> 12:57.611
Let, let me be here for you.

13:01.156 --> 13:02.241
No, no, no, no.

13:02.241 --> 13:05.077
That was not, That was not the--
- Oh. I thought, um--

13:05.077 --> 13:06.995
I mean, you really made it
seem like you wanted that.

13:06.995 --> 13:08.830
- No. No, Liam, Liam,
I, I, I just wanted to help.

13:08.830 --> 13:10.123
- I didn't ask for your help!

13:10.123 --> 13:12.125
♪ tense music playing ♪

13:13.794 --> 13:15.796
Why couldn't you have just left me alone?

13:22.886 --> 13:24.763
[TV playing]

13:25.389 --> 13:27.307
- Hey, Mama. You look nice.

13:27.307 --> 13:30.269
- Thank you. Going to evening mass.

13:31.603 --> 13:33.230
- What's goin' on with Dad?

13:34.898 --> 13:36.483
- I think your sister broke him.

13:36.483 --> 13:37.734
[chuckles]

13:38.944 --> 13:40.153
- Can I go to church with you?

13:41.280 --> 13:44.116
- Is this happening? Is this a dream?

13:44.658 --> 13:47.286
- Please don't make a big deal outta this.
- Oh, gracias a dios.

13:47.286 --> 13:49.162
I never thought I'd see the day.

13:49.162 --> 13:51.999
- I'm gonna go grab my jacket, so.
- Hurry, let's go.

13:54.501 --> 13:55.502
I did it!

14:00.591 --> 14:02.217
- Oh, I was just about
to bring you your club soda.

14:02.217 --> 14:03.677
- It's fine... really.

14:04.344 --> 14:08.015
Look, I am so sorry if
I was intense back there.

14:08.015 --> 14:10.142
Weird night.
One of those "fake date your bestie

14:10.142 --> 14:13.645
to convince your homophobic uncle
that you're straight" scenarios.

14:13.645 --> 14:16.648
- Is your fake girlfriend for hire?
Will she come to my grandma's for Easter?

14:16.648 --> 14:18.942
- [laughs] Um,

14:18.942 --> 14:23.405
it has come to my attention that
I may have missed our meet-cute.

14:23.405 --> 14:25.949
- Ah, no shit.
Nice of you to finally notice.

14:27.242 --> 14:29.077
- Maybe I can get your number?

14:29.077 --> 14:31.079
Before I have to go back
to the old ball and chain?

14:31.997 --> 14:32.831
- Yeah.

14:38.045 --> 14:39.129
I'm Connor by the way.

14:39.963 --> 14:40.797
- Rahim.

14:42.966 --> 14:44.092
- I gotta run.

14:45.969 --> 14:49.389
♪ upbeat music playing ♪

14:49.389 --> 14:53.602
- So, Pilar, tell me, how did Rahim
convince a wonderful girl like you

14:53.602 --> 14:54.603
to go out with him?

14:55.395 --> 14:57.606
That's a joke.
PILAR: Oh, I, I don't know.

15:02.361 --> 15:08.283
- Uh-oh. You're under Lake's weighted
blanket cuddling a... creepy doll.

15:08.283 --> 15:10.410
- Mm, I knitted it for the baby.

15:11.620 --> 15:14.289
- Well, come on...
I got a surprise for you.

15:16.917 --> 15:18.627
- Okay. [chuckles]

15:18.627 --> 15:20.629
Okay.
- This will be worth it. I promise.

15:23.048 --> 15:25.425
- Hi!
- Hey, honey!

15:25.425 --> 15:27.261
- Oh my god.

15:27.761 --> 15:29.429
- Hey, listen,
I would've called you earlier,

15:29.429 --> 15:32.599
but this one... had me running
around looking for ice chips.

15:32.599 --> 15:35.352
- "This one" is about
to deliver your baby.

15:35.352 --> 15:37.062
- I know, I know.

15:37.688 --> 15:40.274
- [chuckles] How did you do this?

15:41.191 --> 15:44.027
- I called the hospital
and used my undeniable charm

15:44.027 --> 15:47.364
to convince a lovely nurse
named Diane to bring in an iPad.

15:47.364 --> 15:50.784
- Uh, he Venmo'd her a hundred bucks.
- Yeah, it's charming in its own way.

15:55.622 --> 15:56.623
- Thank you.

15:56.623 --> 15:58.792
- Okay, we can all agree
that this is very romantic,

15:58.792 --> 16:00.836
but this is called FaceTime,
not VaginaTime.

16:00.836 --> 16:02.504
Just bring it up.
[laughing]

16:02.504 --> 16:04.381
I'm serious.
Just bring it up and-- Up and in.

16:07.551 --> 16:08.552
- Hi.

16:09.428 --> 16:11.430
♪

16:14.474 --> 16:18.103
- This is nice.
Having you here with me tonight.

16:19.271 --> 16:20.898
- Yeah, it is nice.

16:21.857 --> 16:25.485
- So... why are you here?

16:28.030 --> 16:29.031
- I don't know.

16:30.699 --> 16:35.370
I... guess I always just like
how quiet church is at night.

16:36.580 --> 16:40.375
It's always been a place where I could...
think about the big things.

16:40.375 --> 16:45.297
You know, like...
who I am and who I wanna be.

16:46.882 --> 16:50.010
- Any particular reason you're
thinking about that right now?

16:52.804 --> 16:57.518
- Lately... I feel like all I do is
mess things up for everyone in my life.

16:57.518 --> 17:01.104
Like some sort of
clueless wrecking ball.

17:01.104 --> 17:03.649
- Hey, that's my favorite son
you're talking about.

17:03.649 --> 17:06.485
Oldest. I said, "my oldest son."
[laughing]

17:07.653 --> 17:09.905
Ay, don't be so hard on yourself.

17:09.905 --> 17:12.783
Every teenager is
a clueless wrecking ball.

17:13.575 --> 17:16.370
And the fact that you're
asking yourself these questions,

17:17.371 --> 17:19.206
you're a good man, mijo.

17:20.123 --> 17:22.751
- Yeah, I guess so.
- I know so.

17:25.379 --> 17:27.589
- Victor.
- Nick.

17:28.966 --> 17:31.218
Hey, um, what are you doing here?

17:31.218 --> 17:33.220
- I just finished up youth group.

17:35.055 --> 17:39.101
- Oh, I have to go talk to...
Jesus about something,

17:39.101 --> 17:40.519
so I'll see you in the car.

17:42.604 --> 17:45.566
- Uh, I'm, I'm so glad I ran into you.

17:46.358 --> 17:47.943
I've been wanting to talk to you.

17:47.943 --> 17:52.531
To tell you that I'm... I'm sorry, Victor,
for how I acted when we were hanging out.

17:52.531 --> 17:56.743
- Uh... it-it's fine.
- No, it's, it's not.

17:56.743 --> 17:58.537
You wanted to be more
than just a booty call,

17:58.537 --> 18:00.247
and I didn't even give it a shot.

18:00.831 --> 18:05.794
Um, but anyway... I'm, I'm sorry, Victor.

18:05.794 --> 18:09.339
- Like I, I said, it's, it's, it's fine.
- Okay.

18:10.632 --> 18:14.636
- Well, um... I guess I'll see you around.
- Yeah.

18:19.975 --> 18:21.977
♪

18:33.488 --> 18:35.699
- Hi.
- Hi.

18:38.827 --> 18:39.870
Can you sit with me a minute?

18:41.371 --> 18:44.249
I'm done yelling... I promise.

18:59.056 --> 19:03.477
Your mom and I... we were about
your age when we got together.

19:04.520 --> 19:06.271
And I, I know that
things are different now.

19:06.271 --> 19:07.689
- Yeah, women can vote.

19:08.398 --> 19:10.025
- What I'm trying to say is that

19:11.068 --> 19:15.572
I know what it's like
to be young and in love,

19:15.572 --> 19:16.990
especially when it comes to

19:18.116 --> 19:20.160
sex.
- Can we go back to yelling?

19:20.160 --> 19:22.162
- Well, we thought we were being careful.

19:22.829 --> 19:25.749
But... it only took one slip-up
for your mom to get pregnant.

19:26.375 --> 19:28.001
She was only one year older than you.

19:28.919 --> 19:29.920
- Wait. What?

19:31.630 --> 19:35.634
- We're Catholic, so,
of course, we decided to keep it.

19:37.511 --> 19:39.179
We were terrified at first,

19:39.680 --> 19:41.932
but then, found out she was a girl.

19:42.391 --> 19:44.810
So, we started thinking about

19:44.810 --> 19:48.230
putting her in dresses
and taking her to the park.

19:49.147 --> 19:50.566
We even picked out a name for her.

19:51.483 --> 19:52.317
Camila.

19:54.736 --> 19:58.115
And at four months... we lost the baby.

19:59.491 --> 20:01.577
- Why didn't you tell me this earlier?

20:02.452 --> 20:05.873
- It was a long time ago
and your mom and I barely talk about it.

20:08.125 --> 20:10.127
But I wanted you to know because

20:11.086 --> 20:14.173
I think it's part of the reason
why I'm having so much trouble

20:14.173 --> 20:17.384
with the idea of you and Felix having--
- Please don't say it again, yeah.

20:17.384 --> 20:21.847
- Okay. It's just an adult decision
with adult consequences.

20:21.847 --> 20:25.726
And... I know that
you're becoming a young adult,

20:25.726 --> 20:26.810
but...

20:30.647 --> 20:33.692
I guess sometimes I wish you
would just stay my baby girl.

20:36.111 --> 20:37.738
- I wasn't lying to you.

20:39.156 --> 20:42.326
I got the birth control
just to be prepared

20:42.326 --> 20:45.954
in case Felix and I decided to--
- Pilar,

20:47.080 --> 20:50.501
if you really love Felix,
then you should be together.

20:53.253 --> 20:56.256
Consider your relationship un-forbidden.

20:56.715 --> 20:58.717
♪ light music playing ♪

21:05.724 --> 21:07.476
- Tonight was a total bust.

21:07.476 --> 21:09.937
The only new word
I learned was "repudiate,"

21:09.937 --> 21:10.938
which means--

21:12.314 --> 21:13.482
Damnit!

21:13.482 --> 21:16.026
- Babe, just try to relax.

21:16.026 --> 21:19.571
- How? How, how are you
so chill about this?

21:19.571 --> 21:24.451
This test defines our entire futures
and yet, you don't seem to care.

21:24.451 --> 21:28.080
- Well, actually, it doesn't
define my future, like, at all.

21:28.789 --> 21:30.499
I don't think I'm gonna go to college.

21:31.250 --> 21:32.459
- You're not?

21:36.880 --> 21:39.424
- I have enough credits to graduate.

21:39.424 --> 21:41.552
Like, early. Like, this spring.

21:41.552 --> 21:43.011
And I have a cousin who lives in Portland

21:43.011 --> 21:45.681
who says I can stay with her
until I figure things out.

21:45.681 --> 21:46.890
- Figure what out?

21:46.890 --> 21:49.268
- Like, a job, my own place.

21:50.143 --> 21:52.062
- Wait, wait, wait, so you're, like,

21:52.062 --> 21:54.982
planning on permanently moving
to Portland at the end of the semester

21:54.982 --> 21:57.818
and you didn't think, maybe,
that was worth mentioning?

21:58.777 --> 22:00.779
- I did mention it, um.

22:01.280 --> 22:02.614
The first night we hung out,

22:02.614 --> 22:06.034
I said I was saving up to get out
of Creekwood as soon as possible,

22:06.034 --> 22:07.244
that I felt stuck here.

22:09.413 --> 22:11.039
I know I haven't brought it up since.

22:11.540 --> 22:13.750
It's just, things have been
so amazing between us.

22:14.376 --> 22:16.170
I just-- I didn't wanna ruin it.

22:18.005 --> 22:21.008
MIA [shouts]:
You guys! The baby's here!

22:22.801 --> 22:23.927
- You okay?

22:23.927 --> 22:28.015
- Yeah, yeah. I'm just, um... ruminating.

22:28.015 --> 22:30.767
SAT word. Let's go meet the baby.

22:36.773 --> 22:41.528
- Aw, he's so little.
I just wanna squish his face.

22:41.528 --> 22:44.156
- This calls for Georgina's
best bottle of champagne.

22:44.156 --> 22:45.866
She's been saving it
for "something special"

22:45.866 --> 22:46.909
for, like, a decade.

22:46.909 --> 22:48.869
- You know we can hear you, Lake?

22:48.869 --> 22:51.788
- I definitely meant Georgina's
"sparkling apple cider."

22:53.123 --> 22:55.125
- I'm gonna give you guys a moment.

22:55.626 --> 22:57.711
- Tellin' you, Beans.
You gotta get a whiff of this little guy.

22:57.711 --> 23:00.088
There's nothing in the world
like fresh baby.

23:00.088 --> 23:02.591
- Mm, I wish I could
smell through the screen.

23:02.591 --> 23:05.344
- Oh, oh, Mia, we have to go.
They're moving us

23:05.344 --> 23:07.304
to the maternity ward.
- We-we'll, we'll call you later, honey.

23:07.304 --> 23:09.056
All right? I love you.
[call ends]

23:09.932 --> 23:11.558
- Oh, this is so weird.

23:12.559 --> 23:15.395
I have a brother...
and I've never even met him.

23:16.688 --> 23:18.315
I guess this is what I wanted.

23:19.483 --> 23:21.401
Getting to stay in Creekwood.

23:22.361 --> 23:24.112
- Well... why don't we go meet him?

23:24.821 --> 23:26.573
I'm serious.
We can take the next flight out

23:26.573 --> 23:28.575
and... stay for a few days.

23:30.869 --> 23:34.748
- Yeah. A few days. That sounds perfect.

23:36.583 --> 23:38.585
♪

23:44.424 --> 23:47.094
- I just wanted to tell you there's
some bastani in the freezer

23:47.094 --> 23:48.929
in case you wanted a little dessert.

23:49.680 --> 23:50.931
- No, thanks.

23:54.017 --> 23:55.978
I hate pretending to be someone I'm not.

23:57.688 --> 24:01.108
- I know. I'm sorry.
It was only because

24:01.108 --> 24:02.901
Farzad would never understand.

24:02.901 --> 24:06.321
- I don't care... if he understands.

24:10.075 --> 24:16.081
For years, I wondered if it was possible
for me to be gay and Iranian and Muslim.

24:18.333 --> 24:20.335
And when you and Baba accepted me,

24:22.796 --> 24:25.465
I finally believed
I could be all of those things.

24:26.091 --> 24:28.635
For the first time in my life,

24:28.635 --> 24:29.845
I was proud.

24:36.226 --> 24:38.228
And then you made me hide again.

24:42.482 --> 24:43.692
Never again.

24:47.654 --> 24:48.655
- Never again.

24:52.743 --> 24:55.120
That waiter you were talking
to was very handsome.

24:55.120 --> 24:57.915
- Okay, no, I'm, I'm not doing
this with you right now.

24:57.915 --> 25:00.417
- [laughs] Huh?
I told you your boy would come.

25:01.418 --> 25:02.628
It is written.

25:17.643 --> 25:18.644
PILAR:
Hey.

25:19.061 --> 25:19.895
- Hey.

25:20.979 --> 25:22.689
Are you comin' to see me?

25:22.689 --> 25:26.610
- I just wanted to let you know
that my dad and I made up.

25:26.610 --> 25:28.403
He apologized and everything.

25:28.403 --> 25:31.657
- [sighs] Okay. Oh my god.
All right, that is a relief.

25:32.824 --> 25:36.245
All right, we can finally get back
to being normal... Unpause.

25:38.872 --> 25:40.541
Okay, what-what's wrong?

25:41.291 --> 25:44.127
- It was really easy for you
to pick my family over me.

25:45.462 --> 25:48.423
- No. No, okay? You're wrong.
All right, that was not easy.

25:48.423 --> 25:50.342
That was... brutal.

25:50.342 --> 25:52.761
- Not brutal enough, I guess.

25:54.137 --> 25:55.973
I could've never dropped you like that.

25:58.767 --> 26:00.185
I'm sorry, Felix.

26:01.270 --> 26:02.479
This is over.

26:04.815 --> 26:05.858
- Pilar.

26:10.946 --> 26:13.949
♪ "Youuu" by COIN playing ♪

26:16.368 --> 26:19.329
- Hey... Liam. It-it's, uh, me, Victor.

26:19.329 --> 26:22.541
I, I just wanted to call
and say I'm sorry.

26:23.584 --> 26:25.794
Um, and, and I'm around
if-if you ever wanna talk.

26:26.920 --> 26:31.925
And if you never wanna talk,
that's... that's fine, too.

26:33.594 --> 26:36.221
Either way, I'll, I'll still vote
for you for President one day.

26:36.847 --> 26:40.058
♪ And I know your downfall ♪

26:41.351 --> 26:43.562
♪ Though we fell apart ♪

26:45.397 --> 26:48.775
♪ It was no one's fault ♪
[phone dings]

26:51.153 --> 26:54.907
♪ I've gotta make you remember ♪

26:55.908 --> 27:00.370
♪ How hard it was to let me go ♪

27:00.370 --> 27:04.458
♪ Slow dancing with a stranger ♪

27:07.044 --> 27:08.086
What are you doing here?

27:08.962 --> 27:11.798
♪ But it's always been you ♪

27:11.798 --> 27:13.425
Are those for me?
- Yeah.

27:15.219 --> 27:18.096
Thought you like
this corny, romantic stuff.

27:18.096 --> 27:20.474
- I mean, that's cheesy, even for me.

27:20.474 --> 27:22.684
- Okay, yeah, I overdid it.
[laughs]

27:22.684 --> 27:25.729
Uh, [chuckles]... look, um,

27:25.729 --> 27:28.941
I chickened out at church,
but what I really wanted to say

27:30.025 --> 27:33.987
was, would you like
to go out to dinner sometime?

27:35.614 --> 27:39.076
Uh... you can have these,

27:39.076 --> 27:42.579
and just, just think on it and text me.

27:42.579 --> 27:45.999
♪ She moves just like you ♪

27:45.999 --> 27:49.419
- I'm in.
♪ She tastes just like you ♪

27:50.295 --> 27:52.631
